External package containing the POCO C++ Libraries from [https://pocoproject.org].

POCO is not used by the engine itself.  It is built here, unconditionally,
only so that the Collabora Online (COOL) and CODA applications, which live in
the enclosing tree, can link against it without requiring a system or
hand-built POCO installation.

Only the components used by that code are built as static libraries:
PocoFoundation, PocoXML, PocoJSON, PocoUtil, PocoCrypto, PocoNet and
PocoNetSSL.  The bundled zlib, pcre2, utf8proc, pdjson and double-conversion
copies are compiled in; expat and OpenSSL are taken from the engine's own
externals instead of POCO's bundled copies.

The assembled headers are delivered to workdir/UnpackedTarball/poco/include
and the static archives to workdir/LinkTarget/StaticLibrary.
